nts1.n: AD93 w/ Damsel Elysium: Daēdah's Forecast
nts1.d:
Two hours of leftfield dance and beyond every month from AD 93 boss Tasker and guests. Old 88 Transition shows available on the archive.
From The Host: "Storm Daēdah is brewing in Aquarius. Prophecy, ancestral song, phonetics, forecasts and extreme weather. A dive into Damsel's recent favourites as well as glimpses off of the upcoming secret mixtape 'The Maiden, The Architect & The Mediator'."

nts1.n: Death Is Not The End - Argentine Tangos & Milongas
nts1.d:
Death Is Not The End digs up the oldest of the old, serving up your gospel, blues and folk with a crackle. Hear the dust.
From the host: "A collection of Argentine tangos, milongas & waltzes from the early part of the 20th century into the 1950s."

A hour of music in honor of the late, great Sergio Mendes (1941-2024).
Pianist, songwriter, producer, and responsible for delivering Brazilian music and good vibes to the world for decades.
System Olympia joins us for an hour a month.

nts1.n: No Weapon is Absolute w/ Marius Georgescu (R)
nts1.d: Cosmo Vitelli & DJ Sundae head up the monthly hour-long slot for No Weapon Is Absolute, direct from Paris…

In Iceland, Thomas Stankiewicz contemplates the constant flux of the elements. A composer & musician in his own right, he selectively weaves in between soundtracks, classical music, and evocative ambient sounds, symphonically unveiling untold stories from past and future…
@tommmasi

nts2.n: LIGHT IN THE ATTIC W/ ANGIE QQ (R)
nts2.d: Since starting in a basement apartment in Seattle back in 2001, Light In The Attic has established itself as one of the best and brightest reissue labels around. With releases ranging from D’Angelo to Serge Gainsbourg, Lewis to Betty Davis, Sly Stone to Karen Dalton, LITA prides itself on the breadth of its output.
PAM & Satoshi from the blog Okonkole Y Trompa select 2 hours of records from their collection for NTS.
Swiss reissue experts Bongo Joe celebrate 10 years of releases with a special guest show.

nts2.n: BLUE TRIO RADIO W/ FULL BODY 2 (R)

nts2.d: Hanoi producer Lý Trang presents an hour of vibrant noise.
Melbourne based producer YL HOOI share an hour of dub, electronics, postpunk and more every month…

If you ever need some creative inspiration, take a look at some videos of Timbaland in the studio in his prime, around the early to mid-2000s. You'll see Timbo smiling knowingly as he plays new material to some of the biggest rap & R&B stars of all time, all of whom appear to display a similar range of emotions – confusion, astonishment, befuddled laughter. 
This is testament to the Virginia producer's utterly genre shifting approach to the rhythm and texture of beat-making. No one sounded like him before, and the many who have imitated rarely reach his level. 
This In Focus is selected by Antonine Scali.
Música sentimental for all the sad girls and sad boys.

nts2.n: ROLAS W/ ABE PEDROZA: TRISTES Y ROMÁNTICAS (R)
nts2.d: Abe Pedroza selects an hour of teark-jerking and romantic music from the Spanish speaking world – boleros, ballads, and moody instrumentals – “pairs well with a game of dominoes con los Tíos”.
Naomi Asa on the NTS airwaves, delivering soothing soul and spiritual jazz.

High Jazz* is an independent record label specializing in 70s & 80s soul, jazz & funk. ill Dubio takes the reigns for the monthly High Jazz* show rustling up an hour of choice selections on a Wednesday.
Another transmission of dead mall energy from the later vaporwave era of the 2010s.

nts2.n: KRISTIN KONTROL PRESENTS: OUT OF VOGUE

subtle.d: In:flux Audio are a record label based in Leeds, UK founded by production duo Tik&Borrow. Since the label's inception in October 2013, they have dabbled in multiple dance music styles with the emphasis always being on the tracks being unique, and packed full of bass. Today the primary output for the label is from their Dubstep roster and this is focus of their show on Subtle - giving the artists and remixers chance to showcase their sounds with an hour guest mix, all hosted by label bossman Tik.

I’m a 19 year old DJ and producer from Newcastle upon Tyne, mainly playing and producing music around the 140bpm mark. I started out playing old 2-step and jungle records, before moving my focus to mainly dubstep and grime. Along with my friends Pirata and White Label, I run Newcastle’s only current 140 night, Well Irie.

subtle.d: Kishan is a DJ and Producer currently based in London. Actively involved in the music scene already, he produces and mixes a wide range of genres including UK Garage, Drum & Bass, House, Disco and Afrobeat.

subtle.d: Sessions w/ Amy B is an underground multi-genre music show, showcasing the most prolific guests from all corners of the music industry.

Originally linking up in Wellington and playing shows with the Breaking Beats crew, Swampman and Zero Crumbs have reunited – bringing their smooth mixing and flexible selections to East London. 

In their monthly show, the pair explore the deep, dark, and soulful ends of DNB. Expect fresh underground tunes, deep cut classics, and a bit of banter in Kiwi accents.

dublab.d: “Dying Songs focuses on melancholic electronic music but isn’t limited to that. Sometimes it gets dark, sometimes I try to mix techno awkwardly, sometimes i get nostalgic… I like stuff that’s dreamy, ghostly, pretty and sad. I’ll try out new productions of my own, as well. I’m keeping it pretty open and we’ll see how it evolves.” – Jimmy

dublab.d: It’s the simple things isn’t it? The little things of life. Good food, sunshine, no traffic, dark coffee, 72˚ breeze, telephone off the hook and music every Friday morning a la Daddy Differently & Dirty Dave.
Peak Oil records presents ‘tipping point’; a monthly journey through the record collections of brian and brion. Leaving no good genre unturned, enjoy two hours of esoterica, conversation and guests.
